results.wikipedia_summary: Keyhole sand dollar refers to five living species of sand dollars in the genus Mellita plus the extinct †Mellita aclinensis Kier, 1963. They are found on the Atlantic coasts of the Americas, ranging across the Caribbean Islands (e.g. Bermuda, Jamaica and Puerto Rico), from the southern United States at the north, to the southeastern coast of Brazil at the south.
